 US and many other American countries, the standard system used to measure =
the diameter of cables and wires is the American Wire Gauge.&nbsp;If you wo=
rk with cables, you=E2=80=99ve likely encountered them: while both indicate=
 conductor size, they are not interchangeable, and using the wrong one can =
lead to serious project delays and safety hazards.</strong></p>



