<div id=3D"faq-question-1764325234017" class=3D"rank-math-list-item">
<h3 class=3D"rank-math-question "><span class=3D"ez-toc-section" id=3D"is-a=
wg-the-same-as-mm%c2%b2"></span>Is AWG the same as mm=C2=B2?<span class=3D"=
ez-toc-section-end"></span></h3>
<div class=3D"rank-math-answer ">

<p>No. AWG is a gauge number, while mm=C2=B2 is a direct measurement of cro=
ss-sectional area. They are correlated but not the same.</p>

</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"faq-question-1764325475389" class=3D"rank-math-list-item">
<h3 class=3D"rank-math-question "><span class=3D"ez-toc-section" id=3D"how-=
